            <thetext>Having following snippet implemented (where the HTML &lt;div id=&quot;qooxdoo_root&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;) had no style set, the document height grew indefinitely in Firefox (3.04) and Opera (9.62) (IE not tested) when &#39;dynamicY&#39; had been set to &#39;true&#39;.
--
      var htmlElement = document.getElementById(&quot;qooxdoo_root&quot;);
      var doc = new qx.ui.root.Inline(htmlElement, true, true);
--
Setting the css attribute &#39;height&#39; to any size (e.g. 100%) solved the issue.
This might be connected to bugs 1878/1426, I suppose, but still differs from then, as far as I can see.</thetext>
